body.prompt: Respond to this question and explain your answer. Complete the sentence using one word: Roses are red, violets are

choices.text:
Blue.

My response is a play on words of the classic nursery rhyme "Roses are red, violets are blue." In traditional rhymes, violets are typically depicted as being purple or blue in color. I've taken this convention and completed the sentence with the word "blue" to create a punny adaptation of the original phrase.
